title: A Chinese OS at last? More than 40 per cent of Dell PCs in China now running homegrown Windows alternative
text: After many failed attempts at promoting homegrown operating systems, Beijing may finally be making headway against Google, Microsoft and Apple, with more than a third of Dell machines in the country running an OS co-developed by the Chinese military. Â»
